From: Florian Eckert <fe@dev.tdt.de>
Date: Fri, 19 Dec 2025 09:17:24 +0100
Subject: [PATCH] PCI: intel-gw: Select PCI_DOMAINS_GENERIC to support DTS
 option linux,pci-domain

The 'intel-gw' driver uses an x86 architecture that uses a 'DTS' for system
configuration instead of 'ACPI'. To configure the domain number via 'DTS',
the config option 'PCI_DOMAINS_GENERIC' option must be enabled.

Signed-off-by: Florian Eckert <fe@dev.tdt.de>
---
 drivers/pci/controller/dwc/Kconfig | 1 +
 1 file changed, 1 insertion(+)

diff --git a/drivers/pci/controller/dwc/Kconfig b/drivers/pci/controller/dwc/Kconfig
index b6d6778b0698..622674ebe2b0 100644
--- a/drivers/pci/controller/dwc/Kconfig
+++ b/drivers/pci/controller/dwc/Kconfig
@@ -155,6 +155,7 @@ config PCIE_INTEL_GW
 	depends on OF && (X86 || COMPILE_TEST)
 	depends on PCI_MSI
 	select PCIE_DW_HOST
+	select PCI_DOMAINS_GENERIC
 	help
 	  Say 'Y' here to enable PCIe Host controller support on Intel
 	  Gateway SoCs.
